HEADWORD: Sou
<hw>Sou</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Sous</plw> <pr>(#)</pr> <it>or</it> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[F.
<ets>sou</ets>, OF. <ets>sol</ets>, from L. <ets>solidus</ets> a gold
coin, in LL., a coin of less value. See <er>Sold</er>, <pos>n.</pos>,
<er>Solid</er>, and and cf. <er>Sol</er>, <er>Soldo</er>.]</ety> <def>An
old French copper coin, equivalent in value to, and now displaced by,
the five-centime piece (⟦frac1x20⟧ of a franc), which is popularly
called a <ex>sou</ex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Souari nut</ent>⟦br⟧
